[SN]TITLE[SN]
Wales v Japan rugby match prompts Cardiff travel warning

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An expected sell-out crowd for Wales' autumn international against Japan has prompted a travel warning for Cardiff.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Cardiff council said a full city centre road closure would be in place from 12:30 GMT until 17:30 on Saturday.
Arriva Trains Wales has advised fans going to the game to get into the city at least three hours before the 14:30 kick-off.
Cardiff Queen Street Station closes at 16:00 and St Mary Street taxi rank will also be closed between 12:30 and 17:30.
A queuing system will be in place at Cardiff Central Station after the match.
Saunders Road from the junction with St Mary Street, the whole of Custom House Street and Penarth Road from the junction with Saunders Road to the entrance leading to the back of the Cardiff Central Station will all be closed from 16:00 to 18:00.
Due to Cardiff City's football game with Huddersfield at the Cardiff City Stadium, which kicks off at 15:00, there will be a crowd management operation in place at Grangetown and Ninian Park stations.
The taxi rank on Mill Lane is not affected and will be open as normal.
Buses will not stop in the city centre during the road closures so will relocate to Churchill Way for services heading east, Greyfriars Road for the north and Tudor Street for the west.
